Name: DIGGS, Charles Coles, Jr.
Footnote: Charles Coles Diggs, Jr. resigned on June 3, 1980, and was succeeded by George Crockett on November 4, 1980.

Name: CONYERS, John, Jr.
Footnote: John Conyers, Jr., resigned on December 5, 2017, and was succeeded by Brenda Jones on November 6, 2018.

Name: DELLUMS, Ronald V.
Footnote: Ronald V. Dellums resigned on February 6, 1998, and was succeeded by Barbara Lee on April 7, 1998.

Name: GRAY, William Herbert, III
Footnote: William Herbert Gray III resigned on September 11, 1991, and was succeeded by Lucien Edward Blackwell on November 5, 1991.

Name: HALL, Katie Beatrice
Footnote: Katie Beatrice Hall was elected on November 2, 1982, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the death of Adam Benjamin Jr.

Name: ESPY, Alphonso Michael (Mike)
Footnote: Michael Alphonso (Mike) Espy resigned on January 22, 1993, and was succeeded by Bennie Thompson on April 13, 1993.

Name: FLAKE, Floyd Harold
Footnote: Floyd Harold Flake resigned on November 17, 1997, and was succeeded by Gregory Meeks on February 3, 1998.

Name: MFUME, Kweisi
Footnote: Kweisi Mfume resigned on February 15, 1996, and was succeeded by Elijah Eugene Cummings on April 16, 1996.

Name: PAYNE, Donald Milford
Footnote: Donald Milford Payne died on March 6, 2012, and was succeeded in a special election by his son Donald Payne, Jr., on November 6, 2012.

Name: CLAYTON, Eva M.
Footnote: Eva M. Clayton was elected on November 3, 1992, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the death of Walter Beaman Jones Sr.

Name: REYNOLDS, Mel
Footnote: Mel Reynolds resigned on October 1, 1995, and was succeeded by Jesse L. Jackson, Jr., on December 12, 1995.

Name: TUCKER, Walter R., III
Footnote: Walter R. Tucker III resigned on December 15, 1995, and was succeeded by Juanita Millender-McDonald on March 26, 1996.

Name: WYNN, Albert Russell
Footnote: Albert Russell Wynn resigned on May 31, 2008, and was succeeded by Donna F. Edwards on June 17, 2008.

Name: FATTAH, Chaka
Footnote: Chaka Fattah resigned on June 23, 2016.

Name: MILLENDER-MCDONALD, Juanita
Footnote: Juanita Millender-McDonald was elected on March 26, 1996, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of Walter R. Tucker III.

Name: MILLENDER-MCDONALD, Juanita
Footnote: Juanita Millender-McDonald died on April 21, 2007, and was succeeded in a special election by Laura Richardson on August 21, 2007.

Name: CARSON, Julia May
Footnote: Julia May Carson died on December 15, 2007, and was succeeded in a special election by her grandson Andr Carson on March 11, 2008.

Name: CHRISTENSEN, Donna Marie
Footnote: Donna M. Christensen served under the name Donna Christian-Green in the 105th and 106th Congresses (19972001).

Name: LEE, Barbara
Footnote: Barbara Lee was elected on April 7, 1998, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of Ronald V. Dellums.

Name: JONES, Stephanie Tubbs
Footnote: Stephanie Tubbs Jones died on August 20, 2008, and was succeeded in a special election by Marcia L. Fudge on November 18, 2008.

Name: WATSON, Diane Edith
Footnote: Diane Edith Watson was elected on June 5, 2001, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the death of Julian Carey Dixon.

Name: BALLANCE, Frank W., Jr.
Footnote: Frank W. Ballance, Jr., resigned on June 11, 2004, and was succeeded by George Kenneth (G. K.) Butterfield, Jr., on July 20, 2004.

Name: OBAMA, Barack
Footnote: Barack Obama resigned on November 16, 2008, having been elected the 44th President of the United States on November 4, 2008.

Name: EDWARDS, Donna F.
Footnote: Donna F. Edwards was elected on June 17, 2008, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of Albert Russell Wynn.

Name: FUDGE, Marcia L.
Footnote: Marcia L. Fudge was elected on November 18, 2008, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the death of Stephanie Tubbs Jones.

Name: RICHARDSON, Laura
Footnote: Laura Richardson was elected on August 21, 2007, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the death of Juanita Millender-McDonald.

Name: BURRIS, Roland
Footnote: Roland Burris was appointed to the United States Senate on December 31, 2008, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of Barack Obama; however, Burris's credentials were not in order until January 12, 2009. He took the oath of office on January 15, 2009, and served until November 29, 2010, when he was succeeded in a special election by Mark Kirk.

Name: SCOTT, Tim
Footnote: Tim Scott resigned his House seat on January 2, 2013, to be appointed to the United States Senate.

Name: ADAMS, Alma
Footnote: Alma Adams was elected on November 4, 2014, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of Melvin L. Watt.

Name: COWAN, William (Mo)
Footnote: Appointed as a Democrat to the United States Senate on February 1, 2013, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of Senator John F. Kerry. William (Mo) Cowan did not seek election to the full term and left the Senate on July 15, 2013.

Name: KELLY, Robin L.
Footnote: Robin L. Kelly was elected on April 9, 2013, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of Jesse L. Jackson Jr.

Name: EVANS, Dwight
Footnote: Dwight Evans was elected by special election on November 8, 2016, to succeed Chaka Fattah.

Name: JONES, Brenda
Footnote: Brenda Jones was elected on November 6, 2018, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation of John Conyers Jr.
